It breaks my heart to share this kind of news to everyone. Around 9:30 pm on 12/6/22, we lost @chantylace’s oldest baby girl Jayda in a tragic car accident that occurred in Westminster CA. Jayda was one of the smartest and fearless girls I’ve ever known. Her love and energy she had for everyone around her including my kids never went unnoticed. 18 years old for not even 30 days, Jayda had a whole life ahead of her. Unfortunately it was all taken from her two nights ago. The driver and two other passengers are expected to live but unfortunately we are forced to live life without Jayda. 

Anyone who has met or worked with her mother Chantel knows how often she puts everyone first before herself. She’s been there for her girls since day one and has single handedly gave them both the life they deserved. Day in and day out, Chantel always shows up as a mother, a coworker, a friend, a partner and all the above unconditionally. Now it’s our time to return the favor and let us take on some of the weight for Chantel. 

Her cousin/bestfriend/sister @coc0love3 and myself have started a GoFundMe page to help with some of funeral costs that’ll be coming down the pipeline and anything else that’ll help our family get through this difficult time a little easier. The link can be found in my bio for any donations. Anything helps and will be greatly appreciated. 

Please keep Jayda Jean Feeney, Chantel, baby sister Saige and our family in your thoughts/prayers during this time. Our hearts go out to the other families and kids involved in this horrific accident. Life is so short and unexpected. Cherish every moment you have with loved ones and hold them tight when you have a chance. 

- Nick

One of the coolest projects this year outside my 9-5 has probably been building up a Bronco. Now with 10k on the odometer, this thing has been nothing short of good times and getting to work with brands like @bajadesigns throughout the process has definitely made the adventure more appreciated. Recently BD joined forces with @nittotire to develop a limited edition run of Squadron Sport Lights made exclusively for Nitto Pit Crew members but needed a vehicle to shoot it on. I had the vehicle. I had the tires. I had ALL the lights. We figured it made sense to quickly get involved with this one. Usually you’d catch me behind the lens but it’s always nice when you have talented friends like @jammminjay who can take lead and all I have to do is act like I know what I’m doing. I guess I did something right because shortly after everything launched, I was officially welcomed to @nittopitcrew. Pretty stoked on the captures and the killer opportunity. 🤘🏼

If you want to learn about the build, hit the link in bio to check out “Lighting It Up with Rad Bronco” for a little feature put together by @drivingline! 

#Ford #FordBronco #NewFordBronco #Bronco #BroncoBadlands #Bronco6g #BroncoNation #2022Bronco #RBPitCrew

What a killer ending to a 4 day trip up to Tahoe and back with my @camburgracing buds. With talks of a meteor shower happening on our last night, we pushed south through a heavy storm hoping to catch something on the other side. The skies eventually cleared up, the temps were perfect and the Milky Way shined with a show that exceeded our expectations. I tried to capture some of the action in the sky but once I got this shot, I had to put the camera down to take it all in. 1500 miles of smiles and epic times. Can’t wait for the next one! 🤘🏼

First day of our recent overland trip to Tahoe was a long one but the hidden gem we ended up at around Mammoth was pretty rad for camp and totally worth it. Check out @camburgracing’s full length video on YouTube by hitting the link in my bio if you want to see more.

Day✌🏼of our trip up to Tahoe started off with some pretty epic views for breakfast that offered a taste of Mammoth’s beauty. From there we made our way back down the mountain, headed north on the 395 for a couple hours, took a left onto the 89 for a lunch break at Cutthroat Brewery. Great spot for burgers and beers btw! Got back on the road and made our way into Tahoe for a much needed dip to cool off before ending the day at another rad camping spot. 🏕️

#KMCwheels #CamburgRacing #Magnaflow #Offroad #Overland #MammothLakes #California #Adventure #Offroading

Our last full day in the greater Tahoe area was definitely the highlight of the trip. Lots of dirt miles, high speed lines and good times from start to end. Made our way south through some gnarly weather towards the second half of the day. We pushed through to clear skies by night; eventually finding a spot for camp just in time to experience one of the raddest meteor showers we’ve ever seen. 

A big thank you to @steve_bender for showing us the way and @jerryzaiden having me tag along on another epic trip. Looking forward to heading south of the boarder through Baja in a couple months! 🇲🇽
